'''Medgadget''' is a [[weblog]] about [[medical technologies]]. The website was founded in 2004 and is known for its up-to-date coverage of the international medical technology news, health care trends, and medical research. ''Medgadget'' was launched by Gene Ostrovsky, Nicholas Genes M.D., Ph.D., and Michael Ostrovsky, M.D. in December 2004.

With a reported 750+ thousand monthly pageviews,<ref name="MedgadgetAbout">Self-reported from the [http://medgadget.com/ Medgadget homepage]</ref>''Medgadget''  ranks as one of the world's most trafficked and linked to medical blogs in the world.  [[Fox News]] noted Medgadget as one of the 10 best health blogs in 2010,<ref name=FoxNews>{{cite news|last=Alvarez|first=Manny|title=Best Health Blogs of 2010|url=http://www.foxnews.com/health/2010/12/22/best-health-blogs/|publisher=Fox News|accessdate=14 October 2012|date=December 23, 2010}}</ref> and the site has been described by [[Silicon Valley Business Journal]] as "a popular Web site that focuses on emerging medical devices and technologies."<ref name=Huff>{{cite news|last=Solovitch|first=Sara|title=Docs try Med 2.0|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/sanjose/stories/2007/11/05/story2.html|publisher=[[American City Business Journals]]|accessdate=14 October 2012|date=November 4, 2007}}</ref>  As of October 2012, it has over 7,000 [[Twitter]] followers and more than 5,000 fans on [[Facebook]].<ref name="MedgadgetAbout"/>

